==English==
===Etymology===
Named after Norwegian physician [[w:Gerhard Armauer Hansen|Gerhard Armauer Hansen]] (1841-1912) who in 1873 discovered the bacterium causing the disease.

===Noun===
'''[[Hansen]]’s [[disease]]'''
# The disease [[leprosy]].

